By ADEJUWON OSUNNUYI Lagos state governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu has declared the Lekki toll gates free for motorists on Thursday, 11 July 2019 at peak periods of the day. The governor made this known just as he inspected drainage channels in Ajah axis. Announcing this on his twitter handle, Gboyega Akosile, the deputy Chief Press Secretary, said the opening of the gates is to assist in getting a good result on the traffic surveys being undertaken. 